@startuml state-tab-lifecycle
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because a tab's life is a composite state machine: a Loaded super-state with
'' kind sub-states, an orthogonal Active/Inactive focus, a live-refresh self-loop, and a red error
'' substate; PlantUML supports composite states, self-transitions, and per-state colour that Mermaid
'' stateDiagram cannot colour per concept. Literal palette hexes: purple #A45BAD = DataScript :doc entity
'' lifecycle, green #67B11D markdown, teal #2D9574 image view, tan #9F8766 plain text, red #E0211D error.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Tab / document lifecycle — one :doc entity in DataScript (keyed by :doc/path)

[*] --> Opening

state "Opening" as Opening #7590DB : [:doc/open path] → :vv/open\nmain reads + sends vv:content

state "Loaded" as Loaded #A45BAD {
  state "Markdown" as MD #67B11D : :doc/kind "markdown"\n:doc/html = rendered HTML
  state "Image" as IMG #2D9574 : :doc/kind "image"\n<img file://path> (no :doc/text)
  state "Text" as TXT #9F8766 : :doc/kind "text"\n:doc/html = <pre vv-plain> (escaped)

  [*] --> MD  : kind = markdown
  [*] --> IMG : kind = image
  [*] --> TXT : kind = text

  state "Error" as ERR #E0211D : :doc/error = message\n(content-view shows .vv-error)
  MD  --> ERR : render/read fails → [:content/error]
  TXT --> ERR : read fails
  ERR --> MD  : next good content\nretract stale :doc/error
}

Opening --> Loaded : vv:content arrives\n[:content/received] → :ds/transact

'' orthogonal focus dimension (which tab is active)
state "Active"   as Active   #line:1F6B53 : :ui/active-path = this path\n(vv-tab-active; body shown)
state "Inactive" as Inactive #DDDDDD : open but not focused\n(:doc/open? true, not active)

Loaded   --> Active   : [:tab/activate] / opened
Active   --> Inactive : another tab activated
Inactive --> Active   : [:tab/activate] this path

'' LIVE-REFRESH self-loop on the loaded document
Loaded --> Loaded : **live refresh** (file changed)\nvv:content → re-transact :doc/html\n(only :doc/*; :ui/* preserved)

'' teardown
Active   --> Closed : [:tab/close]
Inactive --> Closed : [:tab/close]
state "Closed" as Closed #DDDDDD : :db/retractEntity\n+ :vv/close (stop watcher)
Closed --> [*]

note bottom of Loaded #FFF6D6
  ONE entity per path (`:doc/path` is :db.unique/identity), so
  re-opening the same file upserts rather than duplicating, and a
  live edit updates this very entity in place (LWW by path).
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= State / concept |
  |<#7590DB>| Opening (request in flight) |
  |<#A45BAD>| Loaded — the DataScript :doc entity (super-state) |
  |<#67B11D>| Markdown body |
  |<#2D9574>| Image view |
  |<#9F8766>| Plain text view |
  |<#E0211D>| Error substate (:doc/error) |
  |<#DDDDDD>| Inactive / Closed |
endlegend
@enduml
